		<description><![CDATA[well, i do listen and check it out by ear too, the lines start bumping up in my head and I&#039;m trying to nail them asap. It&#039;s great ear training at the same time, and, in my case, it keeps my approach really fresh. For lots of chord changes and a really difficult structure a chart might be handy of course. But combining it with your study makes the benefit is greater :-). You&#039;ve at least trained your ears a bit again. And, it&#039;ll go faster and faster? When I played in Cover bands I always learned the songs by heart without charts, even before the first rehearsal. I still know &#039;m after all these years.]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>well, i do listen and check it out by ear too, the lines start bumping up in my head and I&#8217;m trying to nail them asap. It&#8217;s great ear training at the same time, and, in my case, it keeps my approach really fresh. For lots of chord changes and a really difficult structure a chart might be handy of course. But combining it with your study makes the benefit is greater :-). You&#8217;ve at least trained your ears a bit again. And, it&#8217;ll go faster and faster? When I played in Cover bands I always learned the songs by heart without charts, even before the first rehearsal. I still know &#8216;m after all these years.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
